The paper is about learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses a recurrent neural network (RNN) to encode the top results, which suggests a natural language processing (NLP) component, making cs.CL a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper mentions using feature vectors, which suggests a computer vision (CV) component, making cs.CV a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new model that improves upon existing methods, which suggests an artificial intelligence (AI) component, making cs.AI a possible sub-category.
